3. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) - The paper discusses the scalability of the algorithms on a large cluster, which is a topic of interest in networking and internet architecture. 
4. cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) - The algorithms are designed to achieve high degree of parallelism and minimize inter-processor communications, which is a key aspect of distributed, parallel, and cluster computing. 
5. cs.CE (Computational Engineering, Finance, and Science) - The paper discusses the practical applications of the generated graphs in testing and developing graph algorithms, which is relevant to computational engineering, finance, and science.
